# ==============================================================================
# Fortress IaC — hosts.local (example)
# ==============================================================================
# Custom entries that must survive every Fortress run. Two uses:
#   1. Preserve local routes (dev servers, internal shortcuts).
#   2. Add YOUR OWN blocks for sites the StevenBlack list misses
#      (e.g. mirror domains like en-redgifs.com). Point them at 0.0.0.0.
#
# The contents of this file are merged at the TOP of the system hosts file on
# every execution, so anything here always takes precedence and is never lost
# when the blocklist is refreshed.
#
# Install location:
#   Linux   -> /etc/hosts.local
#   Windows -> C:\Windows\System32\drivers\etc\hosts.local
#
# Format is identical to a standard hosts file: "<IP>  <hostname> [aliases...]".
# NOTE: hosts files do NOT support wildcards — list each domain explicitly.
# ==============================================================================

# Loopback basics (keep these if you start from an empty file)
127.0.0.1   localhost
::1         localhost

# Internal / development hosts
192.168.1.10   dev.local
192.168.1.20   git.internal
10.0.0.5       nas.home

# Pin a service to a specific IP
# 203.0.113.42  api.example.com

# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Custom blocks — sites the StevenBlack list doesn't cover (e.g. mirrors).
# Send them to 0.0.0.0 so they fail to resolve. Add one line per domain.
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
0.0.0.0  en-redgifs.com
0.0.0.0  www.en-redgifs.com
# 0.0.0.0  some-new-mirror.com
# 0.0.0.0  www.some-new-mirror.com
